438
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:59,200
Pulmonary embolism.

439
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:01,560
I have no record of this man.

440
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:05,200
Sorry. Who's actually in charge here then?

441
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,200
That would be me.

442
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:11,560
I've been here since midnight
and I made no such calls.

443
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:16,040
Okay, so let me just get this straight:

444
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:20,000
No one phoned me,
so that was my imagination running riot...

445
00:30:20,080 --> 00:30:24,320
...and you've no record of a patient
of mine who died 24 hours ago.

446
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:27,800
Your hospital's known for losing patients.

447
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,720
Living and dead.

448
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:32,640
What did you say?

449
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:34,800
What did you say?

450
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:39,760
You're quite a creepy person.

451
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,440
Before, I thought you were obstructive
or inept.

452
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:46,080
But now I think you're much more sinister.

453
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:48,760
I think you better leave.

454
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:52,720
-You lying about this?
-Everything okay?

455
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,120
Yeah, thanks.

456
00:30:58,040 --> 00:31:01,960
Here, I'm just off. You can pop
your boss back in his drawer now.

457
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,680
