a couple of questions.

517
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:19,080
-What is, say, six times four?
-Excuse me.

518
00:34:19,160 --> 00:34:22,680
I was wondering, do you suppose
I could get something to eat?

519
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,320
Absolutely.

520
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:28,960
-Why don't we do that right now.
-Thanks. I'd appreciate it.

521
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:31,280
It's 24, by the way.

522
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:34,920
The answer to your question.

523
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:38,440
I was a schoolteacher for 18 years.

524
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:49,320
Minkins, Claude. He was here last year.

525
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,400
He was an ER walk-in.

526
00:34:51,640 --> 00:34:53,440
Fractured carpal.

527
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:56,440
What's that? Ankle?

528
00:34:56,560 --> 00:34:58,240
No, it's a wrist.

529
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:02,560
Let's see. Phone number: 212-000-0000.

530
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:05,120
-That means he's homeless.
-Next of kin?

531
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:07,360
-No.
-None. Thanks, Pat.

532
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:12,320
But he's got an outstanding
balance of $981.

533
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:16,720
What, for x-rays?

534
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,520
Let's see.

535
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:23,320
Radiology was $289, and then the lab work.

536
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:27,120
His bloodwork was another $500.

537
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:30,920
Why the hell is he having bloodwork
when he had a broken wrist?

538
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,640
We'll tell you.

539
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,680
Looks like it's been dumped.

540
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:37,920
Meaning?

541
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:40,160
It's the system. It sucks.

542
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:42,760
There's not enough storage,
so every month...

543
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:45,400
...they have to pull stuff down
to make room.

544
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:48,000
And would there be a hard copy
or whatever?

545
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:50,640
You could try the Records Annex...

546
00:35:50,720 --> 00:35:54,160
...but it'll take you a million years
to get clearance.

547
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:57,680
I'll tell you what.
Can you do another one for me?

548
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:00,040
Dolson, Teddy. Please?

549
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:04,560
All right. I'll do Dolson. Dolson for you.

550
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:07,120
Dolson, Theodore.

551
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:10,880
Undomiciled, conjunctivitis, no next of kin.

552
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,680
Another deadbeat.

553
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:17,040
Outstanding balance, $645.80.

554
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:19,160
This is for lab work too?

555
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,360
Yep. Bloodwork.

556
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,280
For conjunctivitis?

557
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:25,520
I guess not. Let's see.

558
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:27,160
Details.

559
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,560
You sure know how to pick them.

560
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:36,000
I mean, we have been bitching
about this system since they put it in.

561
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:39,720
Let me get this straight.
You're saying someone...

562
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,840
...has deleted all this stuff?

563
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:43,960
What? You mean on purpose?

564
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,440
What the hell are you doing?

565
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:22,440
I'm looking for the file on Minkins.

566
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:25,400
He was here before.
Someone tampered with his record.

567
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:27,800
Anyone see you come in?

568
00:37:32,120 --> 00:37:33,480
Look, Jeff.

569
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,760
There are so many things
about this which are so odd.

570
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,960
Would you include your recent self?

571
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,720
You nailed a fellowship.

572
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:46,280
You're two months away.
You're going to places I could never get to.

573
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:52,160
Anyone finds you in here,
and you aren't going anywhere.

574
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:57,240
So relax, okay?

575
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:00,080
By the way, your mystery man?

576
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:02,760
I called security. They're looking into it.

577
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,520
Okay? Now, come on. Come on.

578
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:11,080
I was fighting my ass off like a gladiator.

579
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:13,560
He didn't have a knife, he had a machete.

580
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:17,120
Did I say six inches?
Fourteen inches long. No lie, man.

581
00:38:17,600 --> 00:38:20,120
The motherfuckers took my scrips and all.

582
00:38:21,080 --> 00:38:24,000
Wait a minute,
what kind of stitching you call that?

583
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:25,360
It's good. It's fine.

584
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:27,680
Bullshit. I'm homeless, not stupid.

585
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:31,120
It looks like the Bride of Frankenstein.
Tell him.

586
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:34,280
Those are terrible sutures.
You're a terrible suturer.

587
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:35,560
See?

588
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,920
I'm gonna make you all happy.

589
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,000
-Jack, can you finish this up?
-Sure.

590
00:38:42,040 --> 00:38:43,920
Good. And what's next?

591
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:47,040
Don't you have
that important reception at NYU?

592
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:50,160
Jesus Christ!

593
00:38:50,240 --> 00:38:52,840
Where you going? I'm in serious pain here.

594
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:56,280
And this motherfucker's 12 years old!

595
00:39:00,120 --> 00:39:01,720
Anyhow, my apologies again.

596
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:04,800
It's not a problem.
You've met the rest of the team?

597
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:07,440
I think so. At the interview.

598
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:10,520
-Dr. Sharma.
-Nice seeing you again, Doctor.

599
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:12,080
-Very nice to see you.
-Thank you.

600
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,240
Dr. Cohen.

601
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:15,080
-Good to see you.
-How are you?

602
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:18,240
-Dr. Breceski.
-Welcome to neurology.

603
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:21,040
And do you know Professor Myrick?

604
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:24,160
Who has nothing to do with this program...

605
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:26,800
...but was here and wanted to say hello.

606
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:31,320
You took care of a neighbor's son.
A cab accident.

607
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:33,400
They said you were terrific.

608
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:37,560
Anyhow, I heard you'd be here
and I just wanted to pass that on.

609
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:39,800
Thank you, it's a great honor.

610
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:41,240
So you're moving on?

611
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:43,760
That's right. I start here in the summer.

612
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:45,480
Well, that's great.

613
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:48,000
If you think that ER was tough...

614
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:50,400
...wait till Jim gets started with you.

615
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:51,880
Right, Jim?

616
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:54,280
Dr. Myrick?

617
00:39:58,720 --> 00:40:01,680
I probably shouldn't,
but can I ask you a question?

618
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:05,560
Certainly.

619
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:11,280
Okay, basically...

620
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:13,640
...white male, forties.

621
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:16,160
Elevated thyroid functions.

622
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:18,840
Enzyme toxicity just off the charts.

623
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,840
Convulsions, high fever...

624
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,360
...pulse, pressure and vitals
in total disarray.

625
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:27,160
Who are we talking about?

626
00:40:27,640 --> 00:40:29,480
It's just a patient of mine.

627
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:34,760
You'd have to rule out meningitis.
Did you do a spinal tap?

628
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:36,760
Oh, no, he died on us.

629
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:39,840
What about postmortem?

630
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:45,120
Believe it or not, we've lost the body.

631
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:48,440
Well, that never helps.

632
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:53,360
Bottom line, without a tap,
you'll never know.

633
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,160
That's what I thought.

634
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,280
Thank you very much.

635
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,400
Sure.

636
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:12,080
I guess I was a big help.

637
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:19,160
So?

638
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:21,240
He's not gonna drop it.

639
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:42,120
I'm headed out.

640
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:50,200
I'll see you later.

641
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:53,920
She's eating very well this morning.

642
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:26,800
How you doing?

643
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:31,160
-You take care of your shift?
-My partner's gonna cover for me.

644
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,760
So what's this guy's name?

645
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,200
Luthan.

646
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:39,680
Dr. Guy Luthan.

647
00:42:43,040 --> 00:42:44,920
You're okay on this, right?

648
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:48,040
It's not gonna go in my memoirs.

649
00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:57,280
You can't handle this...

650
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:59,120
...you better tell me now.

651
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:02,040
Look, I'm in, okay?

652
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:07,600
I'm in.

653
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:24,160
My ears are ringing.

654
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:28,880
Could youjust raise your right hand
and your left leg for me, please?

655
00:43:31,320 --> 00:43:33,040
You don't hear it?

656
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:38,400
In a moment, Mr. Randall,
then we'll get you right back to bed.

657
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:46,640
This is Observation Room B.
We need help, stat.

658
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:49,120
You...

659
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:50,880
...gotta stop...

660
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:52,120
...it!

661
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:55,800
This tape was filmed 22 hours...

662
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:58,800
...after the removal
of a 4-micron spinal section...

663
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:00,520
...at the tenth vertebra.

664
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:02,560
Insertion of an electrical prosthetic--

665
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:03,720
Was followed by...

666
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:07,880
...administration of
I.N. 1 monoclonal antibody and so on.

667
00:44:08,160 --> 00:44:09,840
Patient Number 12...

668
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:13,760
...regained 75 percent operational mobility.

669
00:44:14,040 --> 00:44:18,320
And 26 hours and 14 minutes
after his operation...

670
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:20,360
...his condition is stable.

671
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:27,760
Take it easy, guys. We're not there yet,
but we are getting closer.

672
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:30,120
Those who've been here
from the beginning...

673
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:31,840
...Helen and Billy...

674
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:34,720
...and can remember Patient 1,
know how far we've come.

675
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,280
Don't go wild, but your work,
your suffering...

676
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:40,920
...your sacrifices will certainly be worth it.

677
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:43,120
And like I said...

678
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:44,680
...we're not there yet...

679
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:46,960
...but we certainly will be there.

680
00:44:47,080 --> 00:44:48,680
Thank you so much.

681
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:56,240
Literally hundreds of dollars worth...

682
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:59,200
...of unnecessary lab work
wiped off the computer.

683
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:01,960
And Jeff has access to that computer.

684
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:04,440
So I go to the Records Annex to look....

685
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:08,800
I shouldn't be there. To see if there's
a hard copy of details of this lab work.

686
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:10,400
And there's Jeff again.

687
00:45:10,480 --> 00:45:14,080
This time, making pretty unsubtle threats
about my future...

688
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:15,800
...if I don't drop it.

689
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:20,680
What do we do? I have no idea
what they're trying to cover up.

690
00:45:20,920 --> 00:45:23,600
But maybe there's something
we should be doing.

691
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:26,320
This isn't what Jeff told me.

692
00:45:27,560 --> 00:45:30,640
-You spoke to him?
-You're pulling over 90 hours a week.

693
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:33,520
I looked it up. It's too much.
People burn out.

694
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:35,160
I'm not overworked.

695
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:37,680
I brought you over. I'm your biggest fan.

696
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:42,440
Jeff may not be a great boss,
but I trust him.

697
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:44,440
Exactly what I'd have said three days--

698
00:45:44,560 --> 00:45:48,560
When you accuse him of conspiracy,
you start to sound a little odd.

699
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:50,880
Yeah, well, okay. All right.

700
00:45:51,640 --> 00:45:54,320
There's no question I am tired.
That's for sure.

701
00:45:54,400 --> 00:45:55,920
But I promise you...

702
00:45:56,000 --> 00:45:58,520
...I'm not cracking up.
I tell you what I'll do.

703
00:45:58,600 --> 00:46:01,800
I'll get you a copy of the original lab work
on Minkins--

704
00:46:01,920 --> 00:46:04,080
Shut the fuck up!

705
00:46:04,800 --> 00:46:06,240
I'm really sorry.

706
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:07,560
I apologize.

707
00:46:08,120 --> 00:46:10,400
I seriously think you should look at it.

708
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:19,440
The cops, they call you, yes?

709
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:22,960
-They still here?
-This morning I hear something breaking.

710
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:25,400
I call 91 1 right away.

711
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:30,040
Guy Luthan?

712
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:38,480
You're Dr. Luthan?

713
00:46:40,360 --> 00:46:42,120
I'm Detective Manning.

714
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:43,840
Sorry about this.

715
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,280
Fuck!

716
00:46:52,440 --> 00:46:53,560
Fuck!

717
00:46:57,320 --> 00:46:59,680
So, did they just break the door down?

718
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:01,600
Looks that way, yeah.

719
00:47:02,920 --> 00:47:05,880
We called. We figured you worked...

720
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:07,840
...at Gramercy.

721
00:47:08,520 --> 00:47:12,120
The responding officers, they got here,
the door was wide open.

722
00:47:12,680 --> 00:47:14,160
So anyone see anything?

723
00:47:14,240 --> 00:47:16,160
You mean a witness? No.

724
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:18,760
You look a little punchy.

725
00:47:22,080 --> 00:47:23,640
Anything missing?

726
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:25,720
I don't know.

727
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:29,040
Like I said...

728
00:47:29,320 --> 00:47:30,760
...the door was open.

729
00:47:30,840 --> 00:47:32,880
It's legal for us to look around.

730
00:47:36,040 --> 00:47:37,560
What do you mean?

731
00:47:39,520 --> 00:47:41,800
You talking about the hospital stuff?

732
00:47:42,280 --> 00:47:46,320
I've been at Gramercy for two years.
All of this was being thrown out.

733
00:47:46,480 --> 00:47:48,960
You mean, the towels and shit, right?

734
00:47:49,080 --> 00:47:50,800
Finders keepers, right?

735
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:54,360
I thought you'd arrest me.

736
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:59,040
I am concerned about the half ounce
of pharmaceutical cocaine we found.

737
00:48:05,320 --> 00:48:07,000
It was next to your bed.

738
00:48:10,680 --> 00:48:13,040
Do you share this apartment with anyone?

739
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:15,800
No.

740
00:48:16,160 --> 00:48:18,400
I have to place you under arrest.

741
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:22,320
'"You have the right to remain silent.

742
00:48:22,400 --> 00:48:25,920
'"Anything you say can
and will be used against you.'"

743
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:28,160
Something's going on here.

744
00:48:29,360 --> 00:48:32,480
'"If you cannot afford one,
one will be appointed to you.'"

745
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:35,960
Watch your head.

746
00:48:57,760 --> 00:48:59,480
While investigating a burglary...

747
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:03,040
...at the defendant's apartment,
police discovered in plain view...

748
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:06,080
...approximately 18 grams of pure cocaine.

749
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:11,160
The state has charges pending
concerning theft of property...

750
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:14,640
-...from the defendant's employer.
-I don't do pending, Counselor.

751
00:49:14,720 --> 00:49:16,240
Talk to me about bail.

752
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:18,120
We think there's a risk of flight.

753
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:19,880
We're asking for $10,000 bond...

754
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:22,040
...and we'd like his passport.

755
00:49:23,080 --> 00:49:24,360
Look, I can help you.

756
00:49:24,480 --> 00:49:26,160
I'm $125 an hour.

757
00:49:26,240 --> 00:49:29,080
It was a bad search. It was a first offense.

758
00:49:29,280 --> 00:49:32,760
For $1,500, we could plead this out,
suspended sentence.

759
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:36,960
Excuse me, where you going?

760
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:38,440
I'm trying to help you!

761
00:49:44,960 --> 00:49:49,200
This is Guy. Ifyou have a message,
leave it after the beep. Thanks.

