1021
01:11:19,800 --> 01:11:21,360
What's the FBI doing here?

1022
01:11:22,160 --> 01:11:24,000
We're working a kidnapping.

1023
01:11:24,160 --> 01:11:26,000
Have you seen anyone back there?

1024
01:11:28,320 --> 01:11:31,840
No, we ain't seen nobody down here, man.
It's just us.

1025
01:11:32,160 --> 01:11:35,800
This man is dying here.
You've got a radio. Call for help.

1026
01:11:36,000 --> 01:11:37,360
Radios don't work here.

1027
01:11:37,480 --> 01:11:40,120
Come on, Doc. Move it.
We don't have all day.

1028
01:11:41,680 --> 01:11:43,600
How'd you know I was a doctor?

1029
01:11:45,680 --> 01:11:47,760
Shit! They're gonna kill us!

1030
01:11:47,840 --> 01:11:49,600
They're gonna kill us!

1031
01:11:52,640 --> 01:11:55,520
Oh, no. I ain't got no beef with you guys.

1032
01:11:56,120 --> 01:11:57,240
Talk to me, Frank.

1033
01:11:57,360 --> 01:11:58,960
Get going. All the way back.

1034
01:11:59,040 --> 01:12:00,840
-I'm homeless.
-Keep your hands up.

1035
01:12:01,240 --> 01:12:02,160
Move.

1036
01:12:02,240 --> 01:12:03,320
Move!

1037
01:12:03,560 --> 01:12:05,520
You stay right where you are!

1038
01:12:06,400 --> 01:12:10,000
If you want me out of here,
just say the word and I'm gone.

1039
01:12:10,840 --> 01:12:12,360
Just take it easy. Frank.

1040
01:12:16,400 --> 01:12:17,480
Shit!

1041
01:12:27,960 --> 01:12:28,760
Jesus.

1042
01:12:37,040 --> 01:12:38,120
Bob!

1043
01:12:39,480 --> 01:12:41,120
You son of a bitch.

1044
01:13:09,880 --> 01:13:11,640
He's getting away! Let's go.

1045
01:13:11,720 --> 01:13:13,600
Come on, Bob! Get going! Move!

1046
01:13:21,920 --> 01:13:24,040
Frank, you gotta help me!

1047
01:13:32,200 --> 01:13:33,360
Come back!

1048
01:13:33,560 --> 01:13:34,960
Get me out of here!

1049
01:13:37,200 --> 01:13:39,080
Hey, what are you doing?

1050
01:15:01,960 --> 01:15:02,800
Dispatch.

1051
01:15:02,880 --> 01:15:04,400
Dispatch. Twenty-nine to dispatch.

1052
01:15:04,480 --> 01:15:06,520
We got a man on the line. He's armed.

1053
01:15:08,600 --> 01:15:10,520
Judith? It's Guy.

1054
01:15:10,800 --> 01:15:13,640
Can you hear me?
If you can hear me, please pick up.

1055
01:15:13,720 --> 01:15:15,680
Please pick up. I know it's late.

1056
01:15:15,880 --> 01:15:17,240
I've been shot.

1057
01:15:17,480 --> 01:15:18,680
You've gotta help me.

1058
01:15:18,800 --> 01:15:22,960
This whole thing, it's real.
There are three men dead back there.

1059
01:15:23,200 --> 01:15:26,240
I swear, it's huge. Judith, please pick up!

1060
01:15:26,560 --> 01:15:30,360
They hijack people from the hospital
and use them for research.

1061
01:15:30,520 --> 01:15:32,520
Triphase is a research program...

1062
01:15:32,600 --> 01:15:35,480
...and someone at Gramercy
is working for them.

1063
01:15:35,560 --> 01:15:37,920
Listen, there's a cop called Stone.

1064
01:15:38,000 --> 01:15:41,280
Call him, he might believe me.
I have to talk to you.

1065
01:15:42,280 --> 01:15:43,320
Are you all right?

1066
01:15:45,120 --> 01:15:47,120
Hey, you're bleeding!

1067
01:15:58,080 --> 01:16:00,480
-Who is it?
-It's Guy Luthan.

1068
01:16:00,640 --> 01:16:02,000
You know what time it is?

1069
01:16:02,120 --> 01:16:04,520
Yeah, I know. I'm sorry. I just....

1070
01:16:04,720 --> 01:16:08,720
-It's 4:00 a.m. What do you want?
-The staff logs, did you....

1071
01:16:08,840 --> 01:16:10,040
What did you say?

1072
01:16:10,160 --> 01:16:12,840
Jodie, please. This is really important.

1073
01:16:22,960 --> 01:16:25,720
You have to be quiet. My brother's asleep.

1074
01:16:27,160 --> 01:16:29,080
My God, what happened?

1075
01:16:29,520 --> 01:16:30,840
I'm okay.

1076
01:16:31,600 --> 01:16:33,240
Oh, my God. That's a gunshot.

1077
01:16:33,320 --> 01:16:35,360
It's okay. It looks worse than it is.

1078
01:16:35,480 --> 01:16:37,960
-You're walking around like this?
-Yeah...

1079
01:16:38,080 --> 01:16:39,440
...I can't go home.

1080
01:16:39,520 --> 01:16:40,760
What happened?

1081
01:16:41,040 --> 01:16:43,840
It doesn't matter.
I can prove this whole thing now.

1082
01:16:43,920 --> 01:16:45,120
Listen.

1083
01:16:45,520 --> 01:16:48,440
You'll come in and you'll be quiet, all right?

1084
01:16:48,680 --> 01:16:51,120
This has to be looked at. Jesus.

1085
01:16:52,040 --> 01:16:53,800
You're losing a lot of blood.

1086
01:16:53,960 --> 01:16:55,240
Where did this happen?

1087
01:16:55,440 --> 01:16:58,440
It's okay. No one knows I'm here.
No one followed me.

1088
01:17:01,840 --> 01:17:02,920
Shit.

1089
01:17:03,680 --> 01:17:05,000
It's okay.

1090
01:17:05,560 --> 01:17:06,920
Someone's here.

1091
01:17:07,080 --> 01:17:08,040
What's going on?

1092
01:17:08,120 --> 01:17:11,400
It's Dr. Luthan from work,
from the hospital. It's okay.

1093
01:17:13,920 --> 01:17:14,960
What happened?

1094
01:17:15,240 --> 01:17:16,520
He was shot.

1095
01:17:20,200 --> 01:17:21,840
Take your coat off.

1096
01:17:23,400 --> 01:17:25,880
The staff logs, are they still there?

1097
01:17:26,720 --> 01:17:27,560
And?

1098
01:17:27,720 --> 01:17:31,320
We'll talk about that later.
You're in shock. You need to sit down.

1099
01:17:32,160 --> 01:17:34,040
Here. Take your shirt off.

1100
01:17:36,400 --> 01:17:40,280
Hold this there. Put pressure on it,
and I'll get a first-aid kit.

1101
01:17:40,440 --> 01:17:41,760
I'll be back.

1102
01:18:28,560 --> 01:18:30,720
So tell me about Triphase.

1103
01:18:53,120 --> 01:18:54,760
I didn't even take lunch.

1104
01:18:54,840 --> 01:18:57,240
I stopped for five minutes
and there's six interns...

1105
01:18:57,320 --> 01:18:59,560
...watching TV, eating popcorn.

1106
01:18:59,800 --> 01:19:01,800
And you've been running all day long.

1107
01:19:01,880 --> 01:19:03,600
Tell me about it.

1108
01:19:03,720 --> 01:19:06,240
What do you know?
You better get his doctor.

1109
01:19:06,360 --> 01:19:07,480
I'm on it.

1110
01:19:16,960 --> 01:19:18,720
-He's coming around?
-Yes.

1111
01:19:18,840 --> 01:19:20,000
You can go.

1112
01:19:30,800 --> 01:19:32,320
Can you hear me?

1113
01:19:35,480 --> 01:19:37,320
My name is Dr. Mingus.

1114
01:19:38,840 --> 01:19:42,040
You're in the Acute Care Ward
at Riverside Hospital.

1115
01:19:42,280 --> 01:19:45,600
You were found five days ago
by the boat basin in Central Park.

1116
01:19:45,720 --> 01:19:47,240
You'd been shot.

1117
01:19:47,560 --> 01:19:51,560
You lost a great deal of blood.
You've been in a coma until today.

1118
01:19:51,840 --> 01:19:55,320
We didn't know who you were till today.
We contacted your family.

1119
01:19:55,400 --> 01:19:57,920
Your brother is flying in
tomorrow morning.

1120
01:19:59,360 --> 01:20:01,320
I need to talk to the police.

1121
01:20:01,640 --> 01:20:04,240
Sure. As soon as you're stabilized.

1122
01:20:08,640 --> 01:20:10,000
I can't move.

1123
01:20:15,600 --> 01:20:17,440
The gunshot....

1124
01:20:17,600 --> 01:20:22,040
As I said, you lost blood. But we have
other problems to look at now.

1125
01:20:24,680 --> 01:20:26,120
Why can't I move?

1126
01:20:27,200 --> 01:20:29,040
I have some tough news, Guy.

1127
01:20:30,680 --> 01:20:33,200
Listen to me very carefully.
Can you do that?

1128
01:20:35,840 --> 01:20:38,560
You sustained a serious blow
to your upper back.

1129
01:20:38,720 --> 01:20:42,640
There was a severe cervical fracture
of the sixth vertebra.

1130
01:20:42,800 --> 01:20:44,160
Somehow...

1131
01:20:44,360 --> 01:20:46,080
...we're not quite sure...

1132
01:20:46,520 --> 01:20:47,800
...your spinal cord...

1133
01:20:48,040 --> 01:20:49,280
...was cut.

1134
01:20:50,840 --> 01:20:53,840
At the moment, you're paralyzed
from the neck down.

1135
01:20:55,080 --> 01:20:57,000
We did everything we could.

1136
01:20:57,120 --> 01:20:58,760
I'm terribly sorry.

1137
01:21:06,600 --> 01:21:08,760
Guy, listen to me.

1138
01:21:09,080 --> 01:21:11,480
This is not the end of your life.

1139
01:21:11,680 --> 01:21:13,160
Not by any means.

1140
01:21:13,360 --> 01:21:16,960
I know it's hard to accept,
but you'll learn to do things...

1141
01:21:17,120 --> 01:21:19,840
...that you wouldn't believe possible
right now.

1142
01:21:20,040 --> 01:21:23,320
You're going to have a different life,
that's for sure...

1143
01:21:23,520 --> 01:21:27,560
...but it can still be a great life
and a fulfilling life, believe me.

1144
01:21:30,400 --> 01:21:33,880
Whenever you feel ready,
you can meet with our counseling people.

1145
01:21:35,680 --> 01:21:38,080
We have an amazing program here.

1146
01:21:40,160 --> 01:21:41,280
Please...

1147
01:21:42,680 --> 01:21:44,040
...leave me alone.

1148
01:21:48,280 --> 01:21:49,840
I'll look in on you later.

1149
01:22:51,920 --> 01:22:53,280
Dr. Luthan?

1150
01:23:06,520 --> 01:23:07,520
Guy.

1151
01:23:09,360 --> 01:23:10,920
It's Dr. Myrick.

1152
01:23:15,560 --> 01:23:17,560
I came over as soon as I heard.

1153
01:23:19,440 --> 01:23:21,560
Dr. Mingus was a student of mine.

1154
01:23:26,160 --> 01:23:29,000
I've seen your chart. It's a terrible thing.

1155
01:23:29,520 --> 01:23:31,360
I'd like to try to help.

1156
01:23:34,560 --> 01:23:36,280
If you want to help me...

1157
01:23:37,400 --> 01:23:38,880
...let me die.

1158
01:23:40,600 --> 01:23:42,440
That's a common request.

1159
01:23:43,000 --> 01:23:44,000
Please.

1160
01:23:44,800 --> 01:23:47,560
Four hundred of potassium chloride
in my IV.

1161
01:23:54,920 --> 01:23:56,440
What if there was hope?

1162
01:23:58,640 --> 01:23:59,640
There isn't.

1163
01:24:14,000 --> 01:24:15,560
What if there was hope?

1164
01:24:17,960 --> 01:24:19,280
What would it be worth...

1165
01:24:19,360 --> 01:24:22,440
...to be able to walk again,
to be able to feed yourself?

1166
01:24:22,800 --> 01:24:24,400
To go back to your old life?

1167
01:24:24,480 --> 01:24:25,960
To be a doctor.

1168
01:24:27,080 --> 01:24:28,680
What would you endure?

1169
01:24:31,360 --> 01:24:32,960
What are you talking about?

1170
01:24:33,760 --> 01:24:35,840
I'm asking you a question.

1171
01:24:37,560 --> 01:24:39,200
What would that be worth?

1172
01:24:41,320 --> 01:24:42,880
I can't live like this.

1173
01:24:45,240 --> 01:24:47,040
With proper care...

1174
01:24:47,680 --> 01:24:49,720
...you can live 20 years like this.

1175
01:24:53,560 --> 01:24:54,960
What would you do?

1176
01:24:56,440 --> 01:24:58,000
What would you risk...

1177
01:24:58,080 --> 01:24:59,600
...to change that?

1178
01:25:02,560 --> 01:25:05,520
I have a C6 break in my cord.

1179
01:25:07,040 --> 01:25:10,360
What if I told you there was a chance
you could be healed?

1180
01:25:14,680 --> 01:25:17,440
That there was a procedure
that offered you...

1181
01:25:17,640 --> 01:25:19,360
...a good chance...

1182
01:25:19,520 --> 01:25:21,520
...that you might walk again?

1183
01:25:24,280 --> 01:25:26,480
What would you do to make that happen?

1184
01:25:32,760 --> 01:25:34,040
Anything.

1185
01:25:36,360 --> 01:25:37,560
Anything?

1186
01:25:47,840 --> 01:25:49,760
You'd better think about that.

1187
01:25:50,960 --> 01:25:52,360
What do you mean?

1188
01:25:53,720 --> 01:25:55,120
What do you mean?

1189
01:25:56,080 --> 01:25:57,040
Wait!

1190
01:25:58,920 --> 01:26:00,120
Dr. Myrick?

1191
01:27:06,640 --> 01:27:07,640
Quiet.

1192
01:27:07,920 --> 01:27:09,320
We have to be quiet.

1193
01:27:09,400 --> 01:27:12,400
You're not paralyzed.
It's an epidural drip. I turned it off.

1194
01:27:12,480 --> 01:27:16,440
You're not at Riverside Hospital.
This is Triphase. You're not paralyzed.

1195
01:27:18,640 --> 01:27:20,400
I don't know how you get out.

1196
01:27:20,520 --> 01:27:23,920
You're on the seventh floor.
There's a hallway just outside.

1197
01:27:25,960 --> 01:27:28,440
Listen to me. You have to get out of here.

1198
01:27:29,440 --> 01:27:31,160
-This is Triphase?
-Yes.

1199
01:27:31,920 --> 01:27:34,440
I found some clothes. Put them on.

1200
01:27:34,520 --> 01:27:35,760
What are you saying?

1201
01:27:35,840 --> 01:27:39,520
I'm sorry. It's just the stitches
from your gunshot. I can't stay.

1202
01:27:39,640 --> 01:27:42,080
-Oh, God, they're looking for me.
-Wait.

1203
01:27:42,960 --> 01:27:44,400
How can you be part of this?

1204
01:27:46,440 --> 01:27:48,000
For my brother.

1205
01:27:48,760 --> 01:27:50,960
I was driving the car when he was hurt.

1206
01:27:54,240 --> 01:27:56,160
Because I was drunk.

1207
01:27:58,040 --> 01:27:59,160
I have to go.

1208
01:28:00,880 --> 01:28:03,360
Just try to get downstairs.

1209
01:28:03,760 --> 01:28:05,200
I'm sorry.

1210
01:28:30,600 --> 01:28:32,800
-But how?
-I don't know.

1211
01:28:33,840 --> 01:28:36,080
They're still warm. He can't go far.

1212
01:28:45,760 --> 01:28:48,240
This is Helen in reception.
What's going on?

1213
01:28:52,520 --> 01:28:54,600
-Luthan's out of his room.
-What?

1214
01:28:54,680 --> 01:28:57,680
-We don't know where he is.
-I'll take the east area.

1215
01:28:57,800 --> 01:28:59,560
I'll grab the other side.

1216
01:29:09,280 --> 01:29:10,880
Don, go to one.

1217
01:29:13,200 --> 01:29:15,440
Stone still want that address
or you going home?

1218
01:29:15,520 --> 01:29:17,360
You kidding? We're going home.

1219
01:29:18,520 --> 01:29:20,080
He still wants it.

1220
01:29:20,520 --> 01:29:22,360
Okay, can you hold one second?

1221
01:29:22,560 --> 01:29:24,880
The guy's a cokehead, for chrissake.

1222
01:29:25,080 --> 01:29:27,600
I told you. He saved my guy. I owe him.

1223
01:29:28,040 --> 01:29:32,680
Okay, Triphase. 403 East 14th Street.
Look for Biosyntex.

1224
01:29:32,880 --> 01:29:34,000
Got it.

1225
01:29:55,280 --> 01:29:56,720
My God.

1226
01:30:10,680 --> 01:30:12,640
I know you can hear me.

1227
01:30:13,160 --> 01:30:15,280
We know you're in the building.

1228
01:30:16,600 --> 01:30:18,400
You've gotta listen to me.

1229
01:30:19,360 --> 01:30:22,800
You need to listen to me
before it gets out of hand.

1230
01:30:23,480 --> 01:30:25,080
Guy, you have to understand.

1231
01:30:25,160 --> 01:30:27,280
We never wanted you involved.

1232
01:30:28,120 --> 01:30:31,000
All the way along,
we tried to get you to walk away.

1233
01:30:31,160 --> 01:30:33,120
I'm not a murderer.

1234
01:30:33,320 --> 01:30:35,200
I didn't know what to do with you.

1235
01:30:35,280 --> 01:30:38,600
It was terrible to put you through it,
but I had to do it.

1236
01:30:39,280 --> 01:30:40,680
I had to make it real.

1237
01:30:41,360 --> 01:30:44,800
You had to feel it to understand
what it is we're trying to do.

1238
01:30:45,560 --> 01:30:47,000
And it is real.

1239
01:30:47,840 --> 01:30:49,800
The hope I offered in that room...

1240
01:30:50,200 --> 01:30:51,360
...it's real.

1241
01:30:51,600 --> 01:30:53,360
I can grow nerves.

1242
01:30:53,480 --> 01:30:56,120
I can grow nerves
and control their patterns.

1243
01:30:56,880 --> 01:31:00,160
Thirty hours before he came to you,
Claude Minkins...

1244
01:31:00,240 --> 01:31:03,960
...had his spine surgically severed
at the fourth vertebra.

1245
01:31:04,200 --> 01:31:06,600
Teddy Dolson lived for 12 days.

1246
01:31:07,280 --> 01:31:09,120
I can show you their charts.

1247
01:31:09,200 --> 01:31:11,040
Complete neural regeneration.

1248
01:31:12,960 --> 01:31:14,360
I can grow nerves.

1249
01:31:14,800 --> 01:31:18,240
Wejust have to stop them overgrowing.
We are that close.

1250
01:31:19,120 --> 01:31:20,880
I needed human subjects.

1251
01:31:21,080 --> 01:31:22,680
That's the awful truth.

1252
01:31:24,080 --> 01:31:26,680
Growth factors only code to species.

1253
01:31:28,480 --> 01:31:31,520
To do the work, you need human subjects.

1254
01:31:32,160 --> 01:31:34,200
And most of them will die.

1255
01:31:35,720 --> 01:31:37,160
These men...

1256
01:31:38,400 --> 01:31:40,040
...they're not victims.

1257
01:31:41,920 --> 01:31:44,120
These men are heroes.

1258
01:31:45,880 --> 01:31:47,320
Because of them...

1259
01:31:47,520 --> 01:31:49,800
...millions ofpeople will walk again.

1260
01:31:51,800 --> 01:31:53,560
You see them every night.

1261
01:31:53,800 --> 01:31:55,560
They're lost or cold...

1262
01:31:55,760 --> 01:31:57,440
...or stoned or worse.

1263
01:31:59,360 --> 01:32:00,760
They have nothing.

1264
01:32:02,000 --> 01:32:03,360
No future.

1265
01:32:03,800 --> 01:32:05,000
No family.

1266
01:32:05,960 --> 01:32:07,000
Nothing.

1267
01:32:08,360 --> 01:32:10,320
But here, with us...

1268
01:32:13,400 --> 01:32:15,440
...here they're performing miracles.

1269
01:32:17,800 --> 01:32:20,280
I've spent time learning about you.

1270
01:32:20,960 --> 01:32:24,080
You're a brilliant doctor. I'm understaffed.

1271
01:32:24,400 --> 01:32:25,720
I need you.

1272
01:32:25,960 --> 01:32:27,600
That's why you're here.

1273
01:32:28,200 --> 01:32:30,320
That's why I put you through this.

1274
01:32:31,760 --> 01:32:33,360
Let me show you what we do.

1275
01:32:34,000 --> 01:32:35,520
Let me explain it to you.

1276
01:32:35,720 --> 01:32:38,080
We need to talk. We need--

1277
01:32:38,960 --> 01:32:40,480
Hey, how you doing?

1278
01:32:41,320 --> 01:32:43,680
You need to see what it is we're doing.

1279
01:32:50,960 --> 01:32:53,800
There's a Detective Stone down here.

1280
01:32:54,040 --> 01:32:57,240
He'd like very much to speak
with someone in charge.

1281
01:32:59,880 --> 01:33:01,200
Someone's coming down.

1282
01:33:01,360 --> 01:33:02,360
Great.

1283
01:33:03,880 --> 01:33:06,280
Lock these doors. She stays here.

1284
01:33:08,720 --> 01:33:12,080
I don't want him leaving here alive.
Find him, okay?

1285
01:34:04,200 --> 01:34:05,040
Gentlemen...

1286
01:34:05,120 --> 01:34:06,600
...how do you do?

1287
01:34:06,880 --> 01:34:09,600
I'm Dr. Myrick. How can I help you?

1288
01:34:23,200 --> 01:34:24,920
This is Triphase.

1289
01:34:26,080 --> 01:34:29,680
-You've got the right place.
-And it wasn't easy. It took us--

1290
01:34:29,840 --> 01:34:33,360
Had a guy, spent four hours
trying to get your phone number.

1291
01:34:34,280 --> 01:34:36,240
So let me get this straight.

1292
01:34:36,360 --> 01:34:40,080
Triphase is like a part of Biosyntex, right?

1293
01:34:40,360 --> 01:34:44,600
That's it. Yes. Look, I'm right
in the middle of a procedure upstairs.

1294
01:34:44,680 --> 01:34:46,000
Could we....

1295
01:34:58,200 --> 01:35:01,400
You know a Dr. Judith Gruszynski?

1296
01:35:01,640 --> 01:35:03,120
From Gramercy Hospital.

1297
01:35:03,200 --> 01:35:05,120
-Is she all right?
-She's fine.

1298
01:35:05,720 --> 01:35:09,560
She got this nutty call from a guy
named Luthan. Dr. Luthan.

1299
01:35:09,640 --> 01:35:11,000
You know him?

1300
01:35:12,440 --> 01:35:13,480
Is he a student?

1301
01:35:13,840 --> 01:35:16,080
No, he's in Emergency. He's a Brit.

1302
01:35:39,440 --> 01:35:41,400
Did you check the scrub room?

1303
01:35:41,480 --> 01:35:42,640
Nothing.

1304
01:35:43,720 --> 01:35:45,000
Do it again.

1305
01:35:45,520 --> 01:35:46,880
I'm going down.

1306
01:36:12,640 --> 01:36:15,200
Can I ask what the hell you do here?

1307
01:36:15,840 --> 01:36:18,680
Research. Medical research.
I'm a neurologist.

1308
01:36:18,800 --> 01:36:20,160
Is that right?

1309
01:36:34,240 --> 01:36:37,160
Are you talking about the doctor
arrested for drugs?

1310
01:36:37,320 --> 01:36:38,520
That's right.

1311
01:36:48,680 --> 01:36:50,640
I really do need to get upstairs.

1312
01:36:50,720 --> 01:36:53,360
We're freezing samples.
It's a delicate procedure.

1313
01:36:53,440 --> 01:36:55,200
We gotta get a statement.

1314
01:36:55,400 --> 01:36:58,080
Later? Could I call you?
Or come by the precinct?

1315
01:37:13,800 --> 01:37:15,120
You know...

1316
01:37:16,920 --> 01:37:19,320
...I'll be done here in about 45 minutes.

1317
01:37:19,560 --> 01:37:21,360
All right. We'll eat.

1318
01:37:21,520 --> 01:37:22,600
Perfect.

1319
01:37:33,560 --> 01:37:35,160
It's nerves, right?

1320
01:37:37,520 --> 01:37:38,440
Excuse me?

1321
01:37:38,520 --> 01:37:40,240
Neurology. It's...

1322
01:37:40,520 --> 01:37:42,240
...study of nerves.

1323
01:37:42,760 --> 01:37:44,280
Yes, nerves.

1324
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:35,480
Are the doors locked?

1325
01:38:38,040 --> 01:38:39,040
No.

1326
01:38:53,440 --> 01:38:55,800
I'm 68 years old. I don't have much time.

1327
01:38:58,680 --> 01:39:00,760
Three years with a rat to get to a dog?

1328
01:39:00,880 --> 01:39:04,760
And after five years, if I'm lucky,
maybe I can work on a chimp?

1329
01:39:05,720 --> 01:39:07,520
We have to move faster than that.

1330
01:39:09,200 --> 01:39:11,400
I'm doing medicine
no one's ever dreamed of.

1331
01:39:11,600 --> 01:39:13,960
This is baseline neural chemistry.

1332
01:39:15,920 --> 01:39:17,080
You're killing people.

1333
01:39:18,600 --> 01:39:21,200
People die every day.
For what? For nothing.

1334
01:39:21,320 --> 01:39:23,280
Plane crash. Train wreck.

1335
01:39:24,080 --> 01:39:26,440
Bosnia. Pick your tragedy.

1336
01:39:27,120 --> 01:39:30,560
Sniper in a restaurant, 15 dead.
Story at 1 1:00. What do we do?

1337
01:39:30,960 --> 01:39:32,520
What do you do?

1338
01:39:33,120 --> 01:39:36,240
You change the channel.
You move on to the next patient.

1339
01:39:37,560 --> 01:39:40,640
You take care of the ones
you think you can save.

1340
01:39:45,200 --> 01:39:46,880
Good doctors do the correct thing.

1341
01:39:46,960 --> 01:39:50,600
Great doctors have the guts
to do the right thing.

1342
01:39:52,720 --> 01:39:54,400
Your father had those guts.

1343
01:39:55,440 --> 01:39:56,720
So do you.

1344
01:39:58,200 --> 01:40:00,800
Two patients on either side.
One, a gold-shield cop...

1345
01:40:00,960 --> 01:40:03,560
...the other, a maniac
that pulled a gun on a bus.

1346
01:40:03,720 --> 01:40:05,560
Who do you work on first?

1347
01:40:06,080 --> 01:40:07,640
You knew.

1348
01:40:09,440 --> 01:40:10,440
You knew.

1349
01:40:12,280 --> 01:40:16,080
If you could cure cancer by killing
one person, wouldn't you?

1350
01:40:16,320 --> 01:40:18,160
Wouldn't that be brave?

1351
01:40:18,840 --> 01:40:21,520
One person and cancer's gone tomorrow?

1352
01:40:27,160 --> 01:40:29,480
When you thought you were paralyzed...

1353
01:40:29,680 --> 01:40:32,640
...what would you have done
to be able to walk again?

1354
01:40:33,440 --> 01:40:34,640
'"Anything.'"

1355
01:40:35,240 --> 01:40:38,000
You said it yourself. Anything.

1356
01:40:40,200 --> 01:40:41,960
You were like that...

1357
01:40:43,720 --> 01:40:45,520
...for 24 hours.

1358
01:40:48,760 --> 01:40:51,320
Helen hasn't walked for 12 years.

1359
01:40:53,560 --> 01:40:55,320
I can cure her.

1360
01:40:56,880 --> 01:40:58,800
And everyone like her.

1361
01:41:04,640 --> 01:41:06,080
The door's open.

1362
01:41:07,800 --> 01:41:09,480
You can go out there...

1363
01:41:09,840 --> 01:41:12,560
...and put a stop to everything
and it'll be over.

1364
01:41:14,320 --> 01:41:17,720
Or we can go upstairs
and change medicine forever.

1365
01:41:19,040 --> 01:41:20,760
It's your call.

1366
01:41:35,880 --> 01:41:37,360
Maybe you're right.

1367
01:41:41,960 --> 01:41:43,920
Those men upstairs, maybe...

1368
01:41:45,440 --> 01:41:47,760
...there isn't much point to their lives.

1369
01:41:50,200 --> 01:41:52,840
Maybe they're doing a great thing
for the world.

1370
01:41:54,320 --> 01:41:56,200
Maybe they are heroes.

1371
01:42:03,360 --> 01:42:05,320
But they didn't choose to be.

1372
01:42:07,680 --> 01:42:08,840
You chose for them.

1373
01:42:11,720 --> 01:42:13,680
You didn't choose your wife...

1374
01:42:14,640 --> 01:42:16,080
...or your granddaughter.

1375
01:42:17,840 --> 01:42:19,760
You didn't ask for volunteers.

1376
01:42:21,560 --> 01:42:23,120
You chose for them.

1377
01:42:24,080 --> 01:42:25,680
And you can't do that.

1378
01:42:26,600 --> 01:42:28,400
Because you're a doctor.

1379
01:42:29,560 --> 01:42:31,160
And you took an oath.

1380
01:42:32,760 --> 01:42:34,440
And you're not God.

1381
01:42:36,120 --> 01:42:39,840
So I don't care if you can do
what you say you can.

1382
01:42:40,680 --> 01:42:43,920
Or if you can cure every disease
on this planet.

1383
01:42:45,080 --> 01:42:48,000
You tortured and murdered
those men upstairs.

1384
01:42:49,640 --> 01:42:52,080
That makes you a disgrace
to your profession.

1385
01:42:53,520 --> 01:42:56,280
I hope you go to jail
for the rest of your life.

1386
01:43:06,400 --> 01:43:07,640
I'm sorry.

1387
01:43:32,760 --> 01:43:34,240
Help him, please!

1388
01:43:34,560 --> 01:43:35,840
Please help him.

1389
01:43:36,000 --> 01:43:37,080
He's been shot!

1390
01:43:37,160 --> 01:43:39,600
Oh, no, no! God, no!

1391
01:43:41,640 --> 01:43:43,280
Help him, he's been shot.

1392
01:44:13,320 --> 01:44:14,720
Help me.

1393
01:44:20,520 --> 01:44:21,840
Please.

1394
01:44:43,120 --> 01:44:44,560
Get some backup.

1395
01:44:48,480 --> 01:44:49,520
You okay?

1396
01:45:25,320 --> 01:45:29,720
I didn't think it was possible,
but your cafeteria is worse than ours.

1397
01:45:29,920 --> 01:45:31,120
I like it.

1398
01:45:31,480 --> 01:45:32,840
I'm sure you do.

1399
01:45:34,000 --> 01:45:37,320
So will you visit us soon,
or are you too high and mighty now?

1400
01:45:37,520 --> 01:45:39,560
I think I'm too high and mighty.

1401
01:45:39,720 --> 01:45:42,440
-I'll come. Soon. How is everyone?
-Pretty good.

1402
01:45:43,600 --> 01:45:45,400
Jodie starts again in the fall.

1403
01:45:46,600 --> 01:45:48,120
Yeah, I heard that.

1404
01:45:49,360 --> 01:45:50,520
That's great.

1405
01:45:51,160 --> 01:45:52,600
She did okay.

1406
01:45:53,160 --> 01:45:56,320
So come visit us.
Don't forget who your real friends are.

1407
01:45:56,960 --> 01:45:59,000
The ones who fired me, right?

1408
01:46:02,040 --> 01:46:03,640
You looked pretty guilty.

1409
01:46:04,040 --> 01:46:06,280
You didn't look unfishy yourself.

1410
01:46:08,560 --> 01:46:09,560
I'm sorry.

1411
01:46:09,960 --> 01:46:11,200
You should be.

1412
01:46:14,960 --> 01:46:18,040
-Take care. Good to see you.
-Good to see you too.

1413
01:46:18,680 --> 01:46:21,200
-Next time, I pick the restaurant.
-Right.

1414
01:46:23,360 --> 01:46:24,560
Dr. Luthan?

1415
01:46:31,200 --> 01:46:33,400
You're from Dr. Cohen's office, right?

1416
01:46:36,560 --> 01:46:38,160
My name is Myrick.

1417
01:46:38,840 --> 01:46:40,080
Ruth Myrick.

1418
01:46:48,480 --> 01:46:50,760
-Would you like to come inside?
-No.

1419
01:46:52,360 --> 01:46:53,360
Thank you.

1420
01:46:55,080 --> 01:46:58,160
I have been trying to decide
what to do about this...

1421
01:46:58,640 --> 01:47:01,040
...ever since my husband's death.

1422
01:47:02,080 --> 01:47:04,120
As far as I can tell...

1423
01:47:04,280 --> 01:47:07,160
...it's pretty much all the data
from his research.

1424
01:47:09,040 --> 01:47:10,880
I think you should have it.

1425
01:47:15,080 --> 01:47:17,400
I believe there's hope in this package.

1426
01:47:20,360 --> 01:47:21,600
Why me?

1427
01:47:22,080 --> 01:47:25,120
I believe my husband was trying
to do a good thing.

1428
01:47:26,720 --> 01:47:28,280
But in the wrong way.

1429
01:47:29,720 --> 01:47:31,200
Perhaps you could do it...

1430
01:47:32,720 --> 01:47:33,960
...the right way.